Here is the complete differentiation process:

$\begin{align}
&\phantom{=}\dfrac{d}{dx}(x^6+3x^4+7x^2)
\\\\
&=\dfrac{d}{dx}(x^6)+3\dfrac{d}{dx}(x^4)+7\dfrac{d}{dx}(x^2)&&\gray{\text{Basic differentiation rules}}
\\\\
&=6x^5+3\cdot4x^3+7\cdot 2x&&\gray{\text{The power rule}}
\\\\
&=6x^5+12x^3+14x
\end{align}$

Here is the complete differentiation process:

$\begin{align}
&\phantom{=}\dfrac{d}{dx}(4x^4-7x^3+3)
\\\\
&=4\dfrac{d}{dx}(x^4)-7\dfrac{d}{dx}(x^3)+\dfrac{d}{dx}(3)&&\gray{\text{Basic differentiation rules}}
\\\\
&=4\dfrac{d}{dx}(x^4)-7\dfrac{d}{dx}(x^3)+0&&\gray{\text{Constant rule}}
\\\\
&=4\cdot 4x^3-7\cdot3x^2&&\gray{\text{The power rule}}
\\\\
&=16x^3-21x^2
\end{align}$

Here is the complete differentiation process:

$\begin{align}
&\phantom{=}\dfrac{d}{dx}(-x^3+5x^2-8x)
\\\\
&=-1\dfrac{d}{dx}(x^3)+5\dfrac{d}{dx}(x^2)-8\dfrac{d}{dx}(x)&&\gray{\text{Basic differentiation rules}}
\\\\
&=-1\cdot3x^2+5\cdot2x-8\cdot 1x^0&&\gray{\text{The power rule}}
\\\\
&=-3x^2+10x-8
\end{align}$

Here is the complete differentiation process:

$\begin{align}
&\phantom{=}\dfrac{d}{dx}(5x^4-2x^3-x^2)
\\\\
&=5\dfrac{d}{dx}(x^4)-2\dfrac{d}{dx}(x^3)-\dfrac{d}{dx}(x^2)&&\gray{\text{Basic differentiation rules}}
\\\\
&=5\cdot4x^3-2\cdot3x^2-2x&&\gray{\text{The power rule}}
\\\\
&=20x^3-6x^2-2x
\end{align}$

Here is the complete differentiation process:

$\begin{align}
&\phantom{=}\dfrac{d}{dx}(-2x^5-3x^3+1)
\\\\
&=-2\dfrac{d}{dx}(x^5)-3\dfrac{d}{dx}(x^3)+\dfrac{d}{dx}(1)&&\gray{\text{Basic differentiation rules}}
\\\\
&=-2\dfrac{d}{dx}(x^5)-3\dfrac{d}{dx}(x^3)+0&&\gray{\text{Constant rule}}
\\\\
&=-2\cdot 5x^4-3\cdot3x^2&&\gray{\text{The power rule}}
\\\\
&=-10x^4-9x^2
\end{align}$

Here is the complete differentiation process:

$\begin{align}
&\phantom{=}\dfrac{d}{dx}(x^3-4x^2+3x)
\\\\
&=\dfrac{d}{dx}(x^3)-4\dfrac{d}{dx}(x^2)+3\dfrac{d}{dx}(x)&&\gray{\text{Basic differentiation rules}}
\\\\
&=3x^2-4\cdot2x+3\cdot 1x^0&&\gray{\text{The power rule}}
\\\\
&=3x^2-8x+3
\end{align}$

Here is the complete differentiation process:

$\begin{align}
&\phantom{=}\dfrac{d}{dx}(-2x^4+3x^3-x^2)
\\\\
&=-2\dfrac{d}{dx}(x^4)+3\dfrac{d}{dx}(x^3)-\dfrac{d}{dx}(x^2)&&\gray{\text{Basic differentiation rules}}
\\\\
&=-2\cdot 4x^3+3\cdot3x^2-2x&&\gray{\text{The power rule}}
\\\\
&=-8x^3+9x^2-2x
\end{align}$

Here is the complete differentiation process:

$\begin{align}
&\phantom{=}\dfrac{d}{dx}(2x^2-6x+5)
\\\\
&=2\dfrac{d}{dx}(x^2)-6\dfrac{d}{dx}(x)+\dfrac{d}{dx}(5)&&\gray{\text{Basic differentiation rules}}
\\\\
&=2\dfrac{d}{dx}(x^2)-6\dfrac{d}{dx}(x)+0&&\gray{\text{Constant rule}}
\\\\
&=2\cdot 2x-6\cdot1x^0&&\gray{\text{The power rule}}
\\\\
&=4x-6
\end{align}$

Here is the complete differentiation process:

$\begin{align}
&\phantom{=}\dfrac{d}{dx}(2x^4+x^3+3x^2)
\\\\
&=2\dfrac{d}{dx}(x^4)+\dfrac{d}{dx}(x^3)+3\dfrac{d}{dx}(x^2)&&\gray{\text{Basic differentiation rules}}
\\\\
&=2\cdot 4x^3+3x^2+3\cdot 2x&&\gray{\text{The power rule}}
\\\\
&=8x^3+3x^2+6x
\end{align}$

Here is the complete differentiation process:

$\begin{align}
&\phantom{=}\dfrac{d}{dx}(x^4-4x^2-10x)
\\\\
&=\dfrac{d}{dx}(x^4)-4\dfrac{d}{dx}(x^2)-10\dfrac{d}{dx}(x)&&\gray{\text{Basic differentiation rules}}
\\\\
&= 4x^3-4\cdot 2x-10\cdot 1x^0&&\gray{\text{The power rule}}
\\\\
&=4x^3-8x-10
\end{align}$
